        <p><MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> supports  authoring and output for left-to-right <MadCap:keyword term="Language support:LTR;LTR languages" />(LTR) as well as right-to-left <MadCap:keyword term="Language support:RTL;RTL languages" />(RTL) languages. This includes English, French, German, Japanese, Chinese, Arabic, Persian, Hebrew, double-byte languages, and more. RTL languages are supported in all outputs except DotNet Help and FrameMaker. <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> supports bi-directional languages not only at the topic level, but all the way down to the paragraph and sentence level. If you have a sentence containing both LTR and RTL languages, <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> will treat each of them appropriately in that sentence.</p>
